      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the crème pâtissière",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the milk with the vanilla pod to just below a simmer. Whisk the egg yolks, sugar, and cornflour until smooth. Pour a third of the hot milk into the egg mixture while whisking, then return to the pan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and boiling, about 3 minutes. Beat in the butter. Press film directly onto the surface and refrigerate until cold and firm, at least 1 hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the flour, sugar, salt, and yeast. Add the milk, eggs, lemon zest, and vanilla and mix until a shaggy dough forms. Knead for 8 minutes by hand or 5 minutes with a dough hook. Add the softened butter in additions and continue kneading until the dough is very smooth and passes the window-pane test, 8 to 10 minutes more. It will be soft. Prove in an oiled bowl for 1 to 1.5 hours until doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape and prove",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Turn the proved dough onto a floured surface and divide into 16 equal pieces (about 60 g each). Roll each into a smooth ball. Place on squares of baking paper on trays, cover, and prove for 45 to 60 minutes until puffy.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fry and fill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oil to 175°C. Fry 3 to 4 bomboloni at a time for 90 seconds per side until deep amber. Drain on a rack. Roll in caster sugar while warm. When just cool enough to handle, poke a skewer into the side of each to create a cavity. Beat the chilled crème pâtissière smooth and transfer to a piping bag with a long plain nozzle. Insert the nozzle into each hole and pipe until the bombolone feels slightly resistant, about 35 to 40 g of cream. Serve within 2 hours.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
